  label="Base Trace: Question: A block of mass 1.00 kg is pushed from rest by a net force of 1.00 Newtons. How far does it travel in 9.00 seconds? Answer (step-by-step): 1.00 Newtons is 1.00 kg m/s^2. So the block will accelerate at 1.00 m/s^2. After 9.00 seconds, it will be moving at 9.00 m/s. The average speed will be 4.50 m/s. The block will travel 40.50 meters. So the answer is 40.50.\n\n                          v12                                           v11                                     v10                                  v9              v8          v7                                 v6       v5       v4                                 v3                                  v2                              v1                             v0";
